The paper discusses the robustness of learning-to-rank-based ranking functions in the context of Web retrieval, which is a core topic in information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also mentions the use of regularization in linear ranking functions, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the manipulation of documents by authors, which is a topic in natural language processing (cs.CL) and cybersecurity (cs.CR). Finally, the paper mentions the analysis of classifiers to adversarial manipulations, which is a topic in computer vision (cs.CV).
